'''朱丽卡·伊凡娜·杜'''（{{lang-en|Julieka Ivanna Dhu}}），通常简称'''杜女士'''（{{lang|en|Ms Dhu}}），出于尊重[[澳大利亚原住民禁忌|原住民人名习惯]]考虑，传媒报导一般不写出她的名字。2014年，年仅22岁的[[澳大利亚原住民|澳大利亚原住民]]杜女士在[[西澳大利亚州|西澳大利亚州]][[黑德兰港|黑德兰港]]警方拘留期间死亡。8月2日，警方获知杜女士的男伴违反[[禁制令|暴力禁制令]]后前往住所将两人逮捕，随后发现杜女士还因欠缴罚款身负逮捕令。她被关进南黑德兰港[[逮捕|警方拘留所]]，因未缴罚款羁押四天。

杜女士在拘留所自称疼痛难忍并被两次送进黑德兰卫生院。医疗人员认为她夸大其辞，可能是毒瘾发作。8月4日，杜女士自称已站不起来。警察指责她无病呻吟，将她铐住后抬上车第三次送到医院，院方不久宣布杜女士死亡，官方公布的死因是三个月前男伴打断肋骨造成感染。

警方经内部调查认定11名警察没有遵守规章或犯有行为失当罪，处以书面或口头警告。[[死因裁判官|死因]]研讯判定警方对待死者“不专业、不人道”，医务人员能力不足。<ref name="inhumane" />研讯报告还称，警方和医务人员所作所为源于对原住民的偏见，建议司法机构不再囚禁未缴罚款人员，推行[[羁押告知服务|羁押告知服务]]。经过多年延误，羁押告知服务终于在2019年10月实施。2019年9月[[西澳大利亚州总检察长|西澳大利亚州总检察长]][[约翰·奎格利|约翰·奎格利]]建议修改法律，停止羁押未缴罚款人员，新法于2020年6月实施。

== 背景 ==
=== 杜女士 ===
1991年12月26日，朱丽卡·伊凡娜·杜生于[[西澳大利亚州|西澳大利亚州]][[黑德兰港|黑德兰港]]<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|5}}，是[[亚马吉族|亚马吉族]][[澳大利亚原住民|澳大利亚原住民]]<ref name="inhumane">{{cite news | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2016/dec/16/ms-dhu-endured-inhumane-treatment-by-police-before-death-in-custody-coroner | title = Ms Dhu endured 'inhumane treatment' by police before death in custody – coroner | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2016-12-16 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201215212334/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2016/dec/16/ms-dhu-endured-inhumane-treatment-by-police-before-death-in-custody-coroner | archivedate = 2020-12-15 | access-date = 2021-02-21}}</ref>。父母在她三岁那年分居，此后她基本是由[[傑拉爾頓|傑拉爾頓]]的祖母养大，父母定期同女儿联系。据称小杜童年生活快乐，身体方面只患有轻度[[哮喘|哮喘]]。<ref name="coroner">{{cite web | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210204032018/https://www.coronerscourt.wa.gov.au/_files/dhu%20finding.pdf | url = https://www.coronerscourt.wa.gov.au/_files/dhu%20finding.pdf | title = Inquest into the death of Julieka Ivanna DHU | last = Fogliani | first = Rosalinda | date = 2016-12-16 | publisher = Western Australian Coroner's Report | archive-date = 2021-02-04 | format = PDF}}</ref>{{rp|5}}据家人所述，小杜念完[[11年级|11年级]]（相同于高中毕业）后<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|5}}开始“与不良分子混在一起”，成了“野孩子”<ref name="paying">{{cite web | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/feature/paying-her-life-justice-julieka-dhu | title = Paying with her life: Justice for Julieka Dhu | year = 2016 | last = Hills | publisher = [[特别广播服务公司|Special Broadcasting Service]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200711141230/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/feature/paying-her-life-justice-julieka-dhu | archivedate = 2020-07-11 | access-date = 2021-02-21 | first = Ben | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

2009年11月，警方发现年仅17岁的小杜在[[电缆海滩|电缆海滩]]昏睡，叫醒时她显然还受兴奋药效影响，赌咒发誓称“吃过[[MDMA|摇头丸]]后啥也不记得”<ref name="paying" />。警方以行为不检、拒不提供姓名和地址将她逮捕并关押一夜。次日保释后她又没有到儿童法院出庭，被处两百澳大利亚元罚款。<ref name="paying" />小杜返回黑德兰港，2010年又牵涉两起涉警轻罪案，其中一次因行为不检被捕时还脚踢女警，随后受妨碍警务及袭警罪指控，法院再度判决罚款<ref name="paying" />。

2013年，21岁的小杜开始和42岁的狄翁·鲁芬交往，此人之前已有孩子，而且小杜不知道法院曾判他[[家庭暴力|家庭暴力]]罪名成立<ref name="paying" />。同年12月下旬，小杜的母亲声称女儿开始变得孤僻而且身型消瘦。小杜告诉母亲，她和鲁芬都在吸食[[甲基苯丙胺|冰毒]]，两人每两周领取一次的[[澳大利亚社会福利联络中心|社会福利金]]一到手就在一两天内用来买毒品。<ref name="paying" />2014年复活节假期前后，小杜告诉祖母鲁芬打她，祖母带她离开鲁芬，买车票把孙女儿从傑拉爾頓送到1100公里外的[[皮尔布拉|皮尔布拉]][[卡拉萨_(西澳大利亚州)|卡拉萨]]投靠亲友<ref name="paying" />。鲁芬发现小杜前往卡拉萨后用几周时间又说服她回去，两人在[[南黑德兰港|南黑德兰港]]租房同居。2014年7月，小杜告诉爸爸说鲁芬打断她的肋骨，鲁芬后来承认，自称是小杜用剪刀刺他的腿在先。<ref name="paying" />

=== 西澳大利亚州拒缴罚款监禁 ===
1991年，[[羁押原住民死亡皇家委员会|羁押原住民死亡皇家委员会]]发布报告提出339项建议，包括不再因未缴罚款发出逮捕令<ref>{{cite web | last = Porter | first = Amanda | title = Why we should honour the humanity of every person who dies in custody | url = https://theconversation.com/why-we-should-honour-the-humanity-of-every-person-who-dies-in-custody-57272 | work = The Conversation | date = 2016-04-16 | archivedate = 2020-10-04 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201004215334/https://theconversation.com/why-we-should-honour-the-humanity-of-every-person-who-dies-in-custody-57272 | dead-url = no}}</ref>，在澳大利亚所有一级行政区（州和领地）实施[[羁押告知服务|羁押告知服务]]<ref>{{cite web | title = Recommendation 224, Royal Commission into Aboriginal Deaths in Custody, 1991 | url = http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/other/IndigLRes/rciadic/national/vol5/5.html#Heading20 | publisher = Royal Commission into Aboriginal Deaths in Custody | archivedate = 2021-02-17 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210217134243/http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/other/IndigLRes/rciadic/national/vol5/5.html#Heading20 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。该服务旨在向受羁押的原住民提供24小时法律咨询和电话支持热线，可与[[原住民法律援助|原住民法律援助]]机构的律师通话。杜女士去世时，澳大利亚只有[[新南威爾士州|新南威爾士州]]和[[澳大利亚首都领地|澳大利亚首都领地]]已经施行羁押告知服务，此后两地截至2014年都从未有原住民在羁押期间死亡。<ref name="cns">{{cite web | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-10-11/indigenous-deaths-custody-notification-scheme/9035876 | title = States urged to back 'life-saving' policy to prevent Indigenous deaths in custody | last = Higgins | first = Isabella | date = 2017-10-11 | publisher = ABC News | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112014804/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-10-11/indigenous-deaths-custody-notification-scheme/9035876}}</ref><ref name="guard">{{cite news | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/mar/09/indigenous-groups-criticise-liberals-and-labor-in-wa-over-custody-policies | title = Indigenous groups criticise Liberals and Labor in WA [Western Australia] over custody policies | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2017-03-09 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210203224712/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/mar/09/indigenous-groups-criticise-liberals-and-labor-in-wa-over-custody-policies | archivedate = 2021-02-03}}</ref>

杜女士去世时，澳大利亚只有西澳大利亚州还在羁押欠缴罚款人员，新南威尔士州自1987年有人在羁押期间死亡后便率先停止这种做法<ref>{{cite news | dead-url = no | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/24/world/australia/police-arrest-aboriginal-woman-fines.html | title = The Police Were Called for Help. They Arrested Her Instead. | last = Albeck-Ripka | first = Livia | date = 2019-02-24 | newspaper = [[纽约时报|The New York Times]] | archivedate = 2021-02-04 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210204031607/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/24/world/australia/police-arrest-aboriginal-woman-fines.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2020-07-11 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://thewest.com.au/news/the-kimberley-echo/big-online-support-for-no-jail-for-fine-default-ng-b88645999z | title = Big online support for no jail for fine default | newspaper = [[西澳洲報|The West Australian]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200711031358/https://thewest.com.au/news/the-kimberley-echo/big-online-support-for-no-jail-for-fine-default-ng-b88645999z | date = 2017-11-08 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。2010至2014年间，西澳大利亚州每年都有上千上因欠缴罚款入狱，该州入狱女子有三分之一是因该项罪名<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/the-point-with-stan-grant/article/2016/03/14/poverty-stricken-women-wa-have-no-alternative-jail-work-fines | title = Poverty stricken women in WA [Western Australia] have no alternative but jail to work off fines | last = Nimmo | first = Julie | date = 2016-03-14 | publisher = National Indigenous Television | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201007010335/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/the-point-with-stan-grant/article/2016/03/14/poverty-stricken-women-wa-have-no-alternative-jail-work-fines | archivedate = 2020-10-07 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。截至2014年，澳大利亚原住民入狱人口有六分之一是未缴罚款，从2008年的33人增至2013年的223人<ref>{{cite news | author = Australian Associated Press | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2014/nov/26/more-than-1100-people-year-jailed-unpaid-fines-wa | title = More than 1,100 people a year jailed over unpaid fines in Western Australia | date = 2014-11-26 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archivedate = 2021-02-02 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210202160008/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2014/nov/26/more-than-1100-people-year-jailed-unpaid-fines-wa}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | date = 2014-11-26 | work = Perth Now | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200725022746/https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/wa-opposition-calls-for-changes-to-unpaid-fines-law-ng-fbbbbb9ad3fdfc14c2751ffc3b9092a2 | dead-url = no | accessdate = 2021-02-22 | url = https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/wa-opposition-calls-for-changes-to-unpaid-fines-law-ng-fbbbbb9ad3fdfc14c2751ffc3b9092a2 | title = WA [Western Australia] Opposition calls for changes to unpaid fines law | archive-date = 2020-07-25}}</ref>。2015年，[[西澳大利亚州州长|西澳大利亚州州长]][[科林·巴尼特|科林·巴尼特]]承认确有数量不明的人因欠缴罚款入狱，数量高于正式文献纪录，因为政府统计只包含入狱，不包括短期警方羁押<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/indigenous/colin-barnett-admits-number-of-fine-defaulters-held-not-known/news-story/ea8fe51af6e5016e0a746350340b52d1 | title = Colin Barnett admits number of fine defaulters held not known | last = Taylor | first = Paige | date = 2015-12-03 | newspaper = [[澳洲人報|The Australian]] | archiveurl = https://archive.vn/20180613145501/https://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/indigenous/colin-barnett-admits-number-of-fine-defaulters-held-not-known/news-story/ea8fe51af6e5016e0a746350340b52d1 | archivedate = 2018-06-13 | access-date = 2018-06-13}}</ref>。2006年中期到2016年中期，西澳大利亚州欠缴罚款的妇女有七成三失业，六成四是原住民<ref>{{cite web | last = Methven | first = Elyse | title = We need evidence-based law reform to reduce rates of Indigenous incarceration | dead-url = no | date = 2020-12-02 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://theconversation.com/we-need-evidence-based-law-reform-to-reduce-rates-of-indigenous-incarceration-94228 | work = The Conversation Australia | archivedate = 2020-12-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201202041249/https://theconversation.com/we-need-evidence-based-law-reform-to-reduce-rates-of-indigenous-incarceration-94228}}</ref>。西澳大利亚州因欠缴罚款入狱将写上刑事犯罪纪录，澳大利亚其他一级行政区都只当民事纠纷处理<ref name="exclusive">{{cite web | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2018/05/09/exclusive-warrant-out-arrest-ms-dhus-cousin-over-unpaid-fines | title = EXCLUSIVE: Warrant out for arrest of Ms Dhu's cousin over unpaid fines | last = Hayman-Reber | first = Madeline | date = 2018-05-09 | publisher = [[特别广播服务公司|Special Broadcasting Service]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102150528/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2018/05/09/exclusive-warrant-out-arrest-ms-dhus-cousin-over-unpaid-fines | archivedate = 2020-11-02 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。此外，西澳大利亚州警方无权酌情忽略未缴罚款的逮捕令<ref name="cousin">{{cite web | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/nitv-news/article/2018/05/11/funny-you-wanted-me-go-jail-monday-warrant-dropped-ms-dhus-cousin | title = 'Funny, you wanted me to go to jail on Monday': Warrant dropped for Ms Dhu's cousin | last = Minshall | first = Jessica | date = 2018-05-11 | publisher = Special Broadcasting Service | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200705062039/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/nitv-news/article/2018/05/11/funny-you-wanted-me-go-jail-monday-warrant-dropped-ms-dhus-cousin | archivedate = 2020-07-05 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

== 逮捕 ==
2014年8月2日，警察接到电话报讯，声称鲁芬违反[[禁制令|暴力禁制令]]；事后调查杜女士死因期间，警察一直没有证实电话线人身份<ref name="paying" />。杜女士尚未成年就曾三次被捕并处罚款，三个月前法院又因她欠缴罚款发出逮捕令。警方抵达杜女士和鲁芬的住所，交谈期间发现她名下的欠款逮捕令。警察逮捕两人并分别关在南黑德兰港警察局的相邻羁押房。杜女士的罚款总额是3622澳大利亚元，被判羁押四天，每天可折算还款250澳大利亚元。<ref name="paying" /><ref name="relive">{{cite news | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/dec/05/family-re-live-pain-as-ms-dhu-inquest-searches-for-answers-over-death-in-custody | title = Family re-live pain as Ms Dhu inquest searches for answers over death in custody | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2015-12-05 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108093444/http://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/dec/05/family-re-live-pain-as-ms-dhu-inquest-searches-for-answers-over-death-in-custody | archivedate = 2020-11-08 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-05-20/jailing-fine-defaulters-wa-prison-overcrowding-report/7433028 | dead-url = no | title = Scrapping jail for fine defaulters will not tackle WA prison overcrowding, report finds | first = Rebecca | last = Turner | publisher = ABC News | date = 2016-05-20 | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023722/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-05-20/jailing-fine-defaulters-wa-prison-overcrowding-report/7433028}}</ref>鲁芬因违反暴力禁制令、盗窃、殴打和刑事破坏数罪并罚，2016年3月还在服刑。西澳大利亚州囚犯审查委员会认为他“对社会构成致命威胁”，故而撤销他的保释。<ref name="paying" />

== 情况恶化并去世 ==
杜女士被捕后自称疼痛难忍<ref name="paying" />，但警方询问时鲁芬就在旁边，杜女士含糊其辞<ref name="blue">{{cite journal | last = Blue | first = Ethan | title = Seeing Ms. Dhu: inquest, conquest, and (in)visibility in black women's deaths in custody | journal = Settler Colonial Studies | date = 2016-09-27 | volume = 7 | issue = 3 | pages = 299–320 | doi = 10.1080/2201473X.2016.1229294}}</ref>。警察给她两片[[对乙酰氨基酚|对乙酰氨基酚]]止痛药，当晚八点把她送到黑德兰卫生院。经过短暂检查，医务人员判定她的[[分诊|分诊]]级别是四，紧急程度倒数第二。检查杜女士的安妮·朗事后接受死因研讯调查，自称当时相信杜女士感到疼痛，但有意夸大程度。她给杜女士开[[羟考酮|羟考酮]]和[[地西泮|地西泮]]止痛，宣布病人情况好转，可以送回警方继续羁押，杜女士不久回到羁押房。<ref name="inhumane" /><ref name="paying" />

根据证词，杜女士接下来20小时哭喊求救、呕吐，请求前往医院<ref name="paying" /><ref>{{cite web | title = Julieka Dhu's death in custody: What you need to know | date = 2016-03-14 | accessdate = 2021-02-22 | publisher= Special Broadcasting Service | archivedate = 2020-08-30 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/the-point-with-stan-grant/article/2016/03/14/julieka-dhus-death-custody-what-you-need-know | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200830052009/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/the-point-with-stan-grant/article/2016/03/14/julieka-dhus-death-custody-what-you-need-know}}</ref>。[[閉路電視|閉路電視]]录像显示他人要求杜女士把疼痛感从轻到重按一至十分级，她的回答是“十”<ref name="inhumane" /><ref name="paying" />。8月3日里克·邦德警佐上班后得知杜女士的病情，他致电杜女士的父亲是否愿意代付罚款换取女儿释放。杜女士的父亲自称没那么多钱，还称女儿吸食冰毒成瘾。邦德接受质询时表示，通过电话后他以为死者当时是在伪装病情想获释，并把上述看法告诉其他警察。当天下午警方铐住杜女士并送到卫生院，医务人员笔记显示杜女士“哭喊疼痛难忍……[[心跳过速|心跳过速]]、惊叫、脱水，心跳每分126次”。<ref name="paying" />因体温计不足，卫生院没有测量体温<ref name="paying" />。分诊护士艾丽丝·希瑟顿告知警方“这可能是脱瘾症状”<ref name="inhumane" />。前一晚目睹杜女士来院治疗的瓦法·纳德里医生用超声波检查后开具对乙酰氨基酚止痛，宣布病情已经改善，警方可以继续监禁，当晚纳德里的笔记上有“行为问题”和“毒品？”字样<ref name="inhumane" />。闭路电视录像显示，杜女士返回警局时，警察口称：“对乙酰氨基酚？就为点儿止痛药搞这么大阵仗？”<ref name="inhumane" />录像还显示邦德将另一人和杜女士关在一起，要求此人好好看看杜女士那副德行：“不要吸毒，否则就会像这个女人一样，这就是下场”<ref name="klip">{{cite journal | last1 = Klippmark | first1 = Pauline | last2 = Crawley | first2 = Karen | title = Justice for Ms Dhu: Accounting for Indigenous Deaths in Custody in Australia | journal = Social & Legal Studies | date = 2017-10-16 | volume = 27 | issue = 6 | pages = 695–715 | doi = 10.1177/0964663917734415}}</ref>。

8月4日，杜女士向警方请求再到医院治疗，自称已站不起来。刚刚换班的雪莉·伯吉斯警员声称，邦德警佐已事先通知，杜女士是“满口谎言”而且“装病”的瘾君子<ref name="paying" />，伯吉斯自称接受邦德的说法，因为“他的话就是法律”，而且邦德面对质疑报以言语攻击的名声在外<ref name="burgess">{{cite web | archivedate = 2020-12-03 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-03-21/ms-dhu-inquest-no-compassion-for-dying-aboriginal-woman-custody/7265066 | title = Ms Dhu inquest: Dying woman shown no compassion; branded 'junkie' by police sergeant | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201203024422/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-03-21/ms-dhu-inquest-no-compassion-for-dying-aboriginal-woman-custody/7265066 | date = 2016-03-21 | publisher = ABC News}}</ref>。她还在作证时表示，邦德曾在杜女士耳边小声言道：“你他妈的瘾君子都已经去过两次医院，门儿都没有”<ref name="paying" />。邦德自称没有当面叫杜女士“瘾君子”，但在与他人谈论时可能说过。他自称曾警告杜女士：“这是最后一次送你妈的去医院。”<ref>{{cite web | dead-url = no | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-03-23/officer-thought-miss-dhu-was-faking-it-inquest-told/7270708 | title = Ms Dhu inquest: Sergeant thought dying woman was coming off drugs while in police cell | last = Menagh | first = Joanna | date = 2016-03-23 | publisher = ABC News | archivedate = 2018-05-30 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180530192623/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-03-23/officer-thought-miss-dhu-was-faking-it-inquest-told/7270708}}</ref>闭路电视录像显示伯吉斯强迫杜女士坐在地上，警察松手后杜女士向后倒，头撞在混凝土地面。伯吉斯在接受质询时声称杜女士当时滑倒。<ref name="inhumane" />中午12点半，邦德第三次把杜女士送到卫生院，伯吉斯与克里斯托弗·马蒂埃铐住杜女士后把她抬上警车后车厢<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|87}}<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/video/2016/dec/16/ms-dhu-death-in-custody-cctv-footage-shows-inhumane-police-treatment-video | title = Ms Dhu death in custody: CCTV footage shows 'inhumane' police treatment – video | date = 2016-12-16 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210204031801/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/video/2016/dec/16/ms-dhu-death-in-custody-cctv-footage-shows-inhumane-police-treatment-video | archivedate = 2021-02-04}}</ref>。闭路电视录像显示她因疼痛呻吟，马蒂埃在旁大小声要她“闭嘴”<ref name="trig">{{cite web | date = 2015-12-23 | title = Police thought dying Aboriginal woman Ms Dhu was faking it, coronial inquest told | first2 = Rebecca | last2 = Trigger | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-11-23/inquest-into-death-of-dhu-in-police-custody/6963244 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201203091426/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-11-23/inquest-into-death-of-dhu-in-police-custody/6963244 | archivedate = 2020-12-03 | publisher = ABC News | first1 = Laura | last1 = Gartry | dead-url = no}}</ref>。抵达卫生院时，马蒂埃又告诉护士“她在装病”<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|89}}<ref name="blue" />，护士听到后表示杜女士心脏病发<ref name="inhumane" />。医务人员尝试急救，马蒂埃在旁继续宣称她在装病<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|89}}。警方将人送到医院53分钟后，医务人员宣布杜女士死亡<ref name="inhumane" /><ref name="paying" />。杜女士是1991年羁押原住民死亡皇家委员会发布报告后第340名羁押期间死亡的澳大利亚原住民<ref name="relive" /><ref>{{cite web | dead-url = no | url = https://thestringer.com.au/340th-death-since-end-of-the-royal-commission-8883 | title = 340th death since end of the Royal Commission | last = Georgatos | first = George | date = 2014-10-19 | work = The Stringer | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200905142908/https://thestringer.com.au/340th-death-since-end-of-the-royal-commission-8883 | archivedate = 2021-02-22 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。

== 死因研讯 ==
[[File:Julieka_Dhu_Protest.jpg|thumb]]

杜女士在押期间的详细情况公布后，她的家人于2014年10月要求开展死因研讯<ref name="distressed" />，呼吁对欠缴罚款不再施以羁押，要求实施羁押告知服务，对所有警局实行24小时医疗保障和独立监督，“为社会公正而非监狱投资”<ref name="castan" />。[[西澳大利亚州绿党|绿党]]议员[[罗宾·查普|罗宾·查普]]支持上述诉求。据称[[西澳大利亞州政府|西澳大利亞州政府]]和警方此时还在调查，准备向死因裁判官递交报告。<ref name="distressed">{{cite web | date = 2014-10-30 | title = Ms Dhu death: Family distressed by details of WA lockup death amid calls for urgent inquiry | first1 = Caitlyn | last1 = Gribbin | first2 = Dale | last2 = Owens | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | publisher = ABC News | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-23/family-distressed-by-details-of-wa-death-in-custody-ms-dhu/5835084 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031048/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-10-23/family-distressed-by-details-of-wa-death-in-custody-ms-dhu/5835084}}</ref>巴尼特州长2014年末在[[珀斯|珀斯]]的集会现场表示同情受害者家属，承诺“彻底公布真相”<ref name="castan" />，但坚称没必要开展死因研讯<ref name="castan">{{cite journal | last = Castan | first = Steven | year = 2014 | title = Downunderallover: Developments around the country | journal = Alternative Law Journal | volume = 39 | issue = 2 | pages = 277–278 }}</ref>。2016年2月，“杜女士盟友”匿名活动组织开始把杜女士和家人的形象投影到珀斯城内建筑，警醒人们关注死因和即将启动的研讯<ref name="blue" /><ref name="klip" />。杜女士死亡一周年之际，澳大利亚各地爆发抗议示威要求调查<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2015/08/04/demands-answers-anniversary-death-custody | title = Demands for answers on anniversary of death in custody | last = Burton-Bradley | first = Robert | date = 2016-10-08 | publisher = Special Broadcasting Service | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200723114117/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2015/08/04/demands-answers-anniversary-death-custody | archivedate = 2020-07-23 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。杜女士之死及其家人的积极活动引发澳大利亚全国传媒关注，此前羁押期间死亡的澳大利亚原住民极少激起风浪<ref>{{cite news | last1 = Wahlquist | first1 = Calla | last2 = Evershed | first2 = Nick | last3 = Allam | first3 = Lorena | title = We examined every Indigenous death in custody since 2008. This is why | archive-date = 2021-02-19 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210219203734/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/aug/28/we-examined-every-indigenous-death-in-custody-since-2008-this-is-why | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/aug/28/we-examined-every-indigenous-death-in-custody-since-2008-this-is-why | accessdate = 2021-02-22 | newspaper = the Guardian | date = 2018-08-27}}</ref>。

死因研讯2015年11月开始。公众收到警告，身穿带有“公正对待朱丽卡”字样T恤者不得入内，两名上衣写有“原住民人权卫士”字样的女子未能入场<ref name="blue" />。研讯第一天出示的证据表明，杜女士去世三个月前被鲁芬打到肋骨骨折，引发[[肺炎|肺炎]]和[[敗血症|敗血症]]致死，死者被捕后的警方闭路电视录像也在现场播放<ref name="inhumane" /><ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2018-06-14 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2015/11/23/inquest-finds-julieka-dhu-died-pneumonia-septicaemia | title = Inquest finds Julieka Dhu died from pneumonia, septicaemia | publisher = Special Broadcasting Service | date = 2015-11-23 | first = Craig | last = Quartermaine | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180614195914/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2015/11/23/inquest-finds-julieka-dhu-died-pneumonia-septicaemia}}</ref>。研讯期间，死者家属、参与治疗的医务人员及十名警察接受质询。受害人之母作证时自称两次致电警局，要求与警方羁押的女儿通话被拒<ref name="trig" />。人权律师[[乔治·纽豪斯|乔治·纽豪斯]]在研讯期间代表[[羁押原住民死亡监护委员会|羁押原住民死亡监护委员会]]出庭<ref name="trig" />。研讯启动后，杜女士的家人遭遇网络暴力洪流，网民谴责死者是犯罪分子，纯属自作自受<ref name="blue" /><ref>{{cite web | dead-url = no | url = https://www.buzzfeed.com/allanclarke/family-disgusted-by-online-abuse-of-dead-woman | title = Family of Woman Who Died in Jail Is Taunted By Cruel Comments Online | last = Clarke | first = Allan | date = 2015-11-27 | work = [[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200808145335/https://www.buzzfeed.com/allanclarke/family-disgusted-by-online-abuse-of-dead-woman | archivedate = 2020-08-08 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。

警方和医务人员作证时一致宣称杜女士装病<ref name="paying" />，伯吉斯自称以为犯人装晕，想让警察快点送她去医院<ref name="burgess" />。调查人员得知，已有11名警察因未遵循正当程序受到纪律处分，警方内部调查还认为四名警察“行为不专业”，面对情况“没有丝毫紧迫感……未能理解情况严重程度并正确应对”<ref name="paying" />。伯吉斯的纪录处分最为严厉，副警察局长以犯人头部撞击混凝土地面后依然“毫无紧迫感”为由向她发出警示<ref name="inhumane" />。三名警察收到书面警告，七人口头警告。这些警告没有马上引起纪律处分，只影响警察晋升几率。<ref>{{cite news | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/dec/03/police-may-have-contributed-to-ms-dhus-death-in-custody-inquest-told | title = Police 'may have contributed' to Ms Dhu's death in custody, inquest told | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2015-12-05 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108091617/http://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/dec/03/police-may-have-contributed-to-ms-dhus-death-in-custody-inquest-told | archivedate = 2020-11-08 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>大部分警察在研讯期间承认不知道这些警告是什么意思，又是出于什么原因。两名警察在受警告后晋升，邦德警佐此时已离开警队，研讯时自称是因“家庭因素”辞职。<ref name="paying" />调查人员询问邦德是否非人对待杜女士，他回答“我看算不上非人，应该说不够专业”<ref name="paying" />。医疗专业人士作证时称，如果警方第二次送杜女士就医时院方准确诊断伤情，她应该就能活下来<ref name="paying" />。[[西澳大学|西澳大学]]农村卫生教授桑德拉·汤普森的证词宣称，如果杜女士是白人中产阶级，警方和卫生院“肯定会花更多时间去了解病情和伤痛，这就是典型的制度种族主义”<ref name="paying" />。资深医护人员甘尼申·萨卡拉帕尼表示，黑德兰卫生院没有制度种族主义文化，即便杜女士是白人，待遇和治疗也不会有任何区别<ref>{{cite web | date = 2015-11-26 | agency = AAP | title  =Hedland Health Campus denies racism against Ms Dhu at Aboriginal death in custody inquest | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/hedland-health-campus-denies-racism-against-ms-dhu-at-aboriginal-death-in-custody-inquest-ng-078c5855077b5593a730a9fb4546dcb9 | work = Perth Now | archivedate = 2020-08-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200817071100/https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/hedland-health-campus-denies-racism-against-ms-dhu-at-aboriginal-death-in-custody-inquest-ng-078c5855077b5593a730a9fb4546dcb9 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

死因研讯由西澳大利亚州死因裁判官[[罗莎琳达·福利亚尼|罗莎琳达·福利亚尼]]主持，2016年12月15日结束<ref name="coroner" />{{rp|165}}。福利亚尼认为警方对待杜女士“不专业、不人道”，“远低于预期标准”<ref name="inhumane" />。她批评警方和院方对原住民心存偏见，受害人第二次就医时得不到合理救治<ref name="inhumane" />，谴责警方在杜女士几乎昏迷时仍然给她戴上手锗之举实在“可耻”<ref name="klip" />。研讯期间，福利亚尼拒绝公开警方羁押杜女士的闭路电视录像，声称受害人隐私比公共利益更重要。裁判官的决定引起死者家属与原住民人权团体反弹，宣称此举旨在“掩盖”种族主义。人们在社交媒体上采用“{{lang|en|#releasethecctv}}”（意为“#公布闭路电视录像”）标签造势，要求公布录像<ref name="blue" /><ref name="klip" />。递交调查结果后，福利亚尼下令公开录像，但死者第三次就医的部分例外<ref name="inhumane" />。福利亚尼的报告不建议刑事起诉警方或医务人员<ref name="klip" />，只建议不再羁押欠缴罚款人员，强制实施羁押告知服务<ref name="inhumane" />。

=== 反响 ===
研讯报告没有指出任何人应对杜女士的死负责，死者家属颇感不满，并向传媒表示有意采取进一步法律行动。西澳大利亚州总警监[[卡尔·奥卡拉汉|卡尔·奥卡拉汉]]承认警方未能有效保障杜女士的安全、福祉和尊严。[[西澳大利亚州原住民司法援助组织|西澳大利亚州原住民司法援助组织]]负责人丹尼斯·艾金顿称死因裁判官的报告“很好”，就是来得太晚。<ref name="inhumane" />巴尼特州长看到研讯报告后表示不会按其中建议行事<ref name="klip" />。

死因研讯报告发布后不久，歌手[[费利克斯·里伯|费利克斯·里伯]]创作颂歌《杜女士》，并制成批评警方和政府行径的音乐视频<ref name="klip" /><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-01-10/the-cat-empire-member-new-song-about-ms-dhu-death-in-custody/8172040 | title = Ms Dhu's death in custody case focus of new song by The Cat Empire's Felix Riebl | last = Day | first = Lauren | date = 2017-01-10 | publisher = ABC News | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112030522/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-01-10/the-cat-empire-member-new-song-about-ms-dhu-death-in-custody/8172040 | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。[[Black_Lives_Matter|Black Lives Matter]]、[[SayHerName|SayHerName]]（“说出她的名字”）和[[Idle_No_More|Idle No More]]（“不再懈怠”）运动组织合作，在互联网上流传杜女士的照片和警局遭遇录像，将原住民公正待遇运动与北美洲及至全世界的人权运动联系起来<ref name="blue" /><ref name="klip" />。

《社会与法律研究》期刊发文宣称，杜女士之死与澳大利亚普遍存在的“性别、制度和结构种族主义”有内在联系，死因裁判官对此视而不见，反而将受害者之死归咎于一系列“个人失误”。文章指出，死因研讯结果表明，只有工作经验最少的警察才把杜女士当人看待，说明此人受西澳大利亚州警队文化荼毒程度最轻。<ref name="klip" />《定居殖民研究》期刊的文章看法类似，批评此次死因研讯不过是殖民者的表演，企图维持他们的征服者地位，根本无法解决杜女士苦难的源头：殖民者仿佛癌症般掠夺社会养分，实际代表父权制和剥削<ref name="blue" />。

== 余波 ==
2015年6月，西澳大利亚州政府宣布提升警方羁押安全程度，努力减少羁押的轻罪或青少年犯人数，但没有说明是否包含欠缴罚款人员。西澳大利亚州原住民司法援助组织认可政府宣告，要求落到实处。杜女士的祖母声称政府声明不足以解决她的担忧，但至少是好的开始。西澳大利亚州惩戒署长[[乔·弗朗西斯|乔·弗朗西斯]]反对任何不再关押欠缴罚款人员的计划<ref>{{cite web | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-24/safer-wa-lock-ups-and-fewer-jail-sentences-after-miss-dhu-death/6570478 | title = Safer lock-ups, fewer jail terms for minor offenders after Ms Dhu death: WA Government | last = Perpitch | first = Nicolas | date = 2015-06-25 | publisher = ABC News | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180224121138/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-24/safer-wa-lock-ups-and-fewer-jail-sentences-after-miss-dhu-death/6570478 | archivedate = 2018-02-24}}</ref>，此前他还曾呼吁对欠缴罚款人员加重处罚，如延长羁押时间<ref name="hilde">{{cite web | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/wa-welfare-recipients-who-avoid-paying-fines-face-longer-jail-time-ng-6b76fcb2b1edf52ca76b4b4261ab646e | title = WA welfare recipients who avoid paying fines face longer jail time | date = 2015-01-13 | work = Perth Now | archivedate = 2020-10-28 | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201028092559/https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/wa/wa-welfare-recipients-who-avoid-paying-fines-face-longer-jail-time-ng-6b76fcb2b1edf52ca76b4b4261ab646e}}</ref>。羁押原住民死亡监护委员会主席马克·纽豪斯指出，弗朗西斯的提议令政府减少囚禁原住民的承诺“形同谎言”<ref>{{cite news | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/jan/13/wa-crackdown-on-fine-defaulters-a-broken-promise-says-indigenous-group | title = WA crackdown on fine defaulters a broken promise, says Indigenous group | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2015-01-13 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200726172620/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/jan/13/wa-crackdown-on-fine-defaulters-a-broken-promise-says-indigenous-group | archivedate = 2020-07-26}}</ref>，西澳大学犯罪学家希尔德·图克斯博士也称，如此提议会令原住民、妇女和贫困人口的处境雪上加霜<ref name="hilde" />。

2016年5月，监禁署督查尼尔·摩根的报告援引杜女士之死，建议西澳大利亚州不再囚禁欠缴罚款人员<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-05-20/jailing-fine-defaulters-wa-prison-overcrowding-report/7433028 | title = Scrapping jail for fine defaulters will not tackle WA prison overcrowding, report finds | last = Turner | first = Rebecca | date = 2016-05-20 | publisher = ABC News | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023722/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-05-20/jailing-fine-defaulters-wa-prison-overcrowding-report/7433028 | archivedate = 2020-11-12 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。2016年10月，[[澳大利亚原住民事务部长|澳大利亚原住民事务部长]][[奈格爾·斯卡良|奈格爾·斯卡良]]提出，任何州如果推行羁押告知服务，联邦政府愿承担前三年费用，但西澳大利亚州政府没有接受<ref name="ex">{{cite news | archivedate = 2021-02-08 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/sep/20/ms-dhus-family-gets-11m-payment-and-state-apology-over-death-in-custody | title = Ms Dhu's family gets $1.1m payment and state apology over death in custody | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2017-09-20 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210208094612/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/sep/20/ms-dhus-family-gets-11m-payment-and-state-apology-over-death-in-custody | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。2017年3月，杜女士家属在[[2017年西澳大利亚州|2017年州选举]]前夕谴责西澳大利亚州两个主要政党不支持羁押告知服务。执政的[[澳大利亚自由党西澳大利亚州分部|自由党]]表态反对羁押告知服务，[[澳大利亚工党西澳大利亚州分部|工党]]表示支持不再羁押欠缴罚款人员，此外只愿意考虑实施羁押告知服务。<ref name="guard" />

2017年9月，西澳大利亚州政府向杜女士的家属补偿110万澳大利亚元并正式道歉，而且不限制死者家属继续采取法律措施，与2017年7月家属在[[西澳大利亚州最高法院|西澳大利亚州最高法院]]递交的民事诉讼也没有关系。杜女士的祖母自称对政府道歉和补偿感到意外，但她更希望看到有人对孙女儿的死负责。西澳大利亚州总检察长约翰·奎格利宣布补偿金额的同时还称有意强制推行羁押告知服务。<ref name="ex" />2017年10月，[[澳大利亚政府|澳大利亚联邦政府]]敦促全国所有一级行政区推行羁押告知服务，奎格利表态支持，声称杜女士被捕后如果有人联系原住民司法援助组织，“结果将完全不同”<ref name="cns" />。不到一周，要求推行羁押告知服务的网上请愿书就有近两万人签名<ref name="cns" />。

2018年5月，法院以未缴罚款罪名向杜女士的堂妹艾丽拉·凯利-莱德发出逮捕令<ref name="exclusive" />。凯利-莱德本来一直按时缴纳罚款，但未能续签就业合同失业后无法继续付款。凯利-莱德经[[众包|众包]]活动筹款还钱时得知逮捕令已经撤回，认为这应该是案件引来的宣传所致，对此她质疑其他欠缴罚款的人是否会有同等待遇。<ref name="cousin" />有消息称，2018年下半年西澳大利亚州议会将提议改革，不再羁押欠缴罚款人员<ref name="exclusive" />。同年十月，奎格利自称会在2019年建议修订法律，不再羁押欠缴罚款人员<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.perthnow.com.au/politics/policy/wa-fine-defaulters-to-have-bank-accounts-wages-docked-under-radical-plan-ng-b88989328z | title = WA fine defaulters to have bank accounts, wages docked under radical plan | last = Campbell | first = Kate | date = 2018-10-14 | newspaper = The Sunday Times | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200705060536/https://www.perthnow.com.au/politics/policy/wa-fine-defaulters-to-have-bank-accounts-wages-docked-under-radical-plan-ng-b88989328z | archivedate = 2020-07-05 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。

2018年5月，新闻报导称西澳大利亚州政府又考虑接受2016年斯卡良的提议，预计羁押告知服务会在2018年结束前开始由西澳大利亚州原住民司法援助组织运作<ref>{{cite news | dead-url = no | url = https://nit.com.au/wa-adopts-custody-hotline-in-wake-of-dhu/ | title = WA adopts custody hotline in wake of Dhu | date = 2018-05-30 | newspaper = National Indigenous Times | archivedate = 2021-01-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210103001009/https://nit.com.au/wa-adopts-custody-hotline-in-wake-of-dhu/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2021-02-11 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.lawyersweekly.com.au/wig-chamber/23368-wa-s-new-24-hour-welfare-line-to-reduce-aboriginal-deaths-in-custody | title = WA's new 24-hour welfare line to reduce Aboriginal deaths in custody | last = Coade | first = Melissa | date = 2018-06-04 | work = Lawyer's Weekly | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210211054616/https://www.lawyersweekly.com.au/wig-chamber/23368-wa-s-new-24-hour-welfare-line-to-reduce-aboriginal-deaths-in-custody}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://junkee.com/custody-notification-service-indigenous/159694 | title = WA Is Finally Taking Steps To Help Prevent Indigenous Deaths in Custody | last = Langford | first = Sam | date = 2018-05-22 | work = Junkee | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200902212454/https://junkee.com/custody-notification-service-indigenous/159694 | archivedate = 2020-09-02 | access-date = 2021-02-22}}</ref>。羁押告知服务因资金问题影响多次延期<ref name="australasianlawyer">{{cite web | archivedate = 2020-09-18 | first = Sol | dead-url = no | url = https://www.thelawyermag.com/au/news/general/kwm-helps-establish-wa-aboriginal-helpline/207401 | title = KWM helps establish WA Aboriginal helpline | last = Dolor | date = 2019-07-09 | work = Australasian Lawyer | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200918051515/https://www.thelawyermag.com/au/news/general/kwm-helps-establish-wa-aboriginal-helpline/207401}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2020-11-09 | access-date = 2021-02-22 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/aug/29/states-failing-to-take-up-lifesaving-phone-service-for-indigenous-prisoners | title = States failing to take up lifesaving phone service for Indigenous prisoners | last1 = Wahlquist | first1 = Calla | last2 = Allam | first2 = Lorena | date = 2018-08-29 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201109043742/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/aug/29/states-failing-to-take-up-lifesaving-phone-service-for-indigenous-prisoners | dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2020-08-20 | url = https://www.als.org.au/custody-notification-service-a-step-closer-to-implementation-in-wa/ | title = Joint media statement – Custody Notification Service a step closer to implementation in WA | date = 2018-11-23 | work = Aboriginal Legal Service of Western Australia Limited | dead-url = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200820153516/https://www.als.org.au/custody-notification-service-a-step-closer-to-implementation-in-wa/}}</ref>，直到2019年10月才启动<ref>{{cite news | access-date = 2021-02-22 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/oct/02/western-australia-rolls-out-lifesaving-hotline-to-address-indigenous-deaths-in-custody | title = Western Australia rolls out lifesaving hotline to address Indigenous deaths in custody | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2019-10-02 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112015022/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/oct/02/western-australia-rolls-out-lifesaving-hotline-to-address-indigenous-deaths-in-custody | archive-date = 2020-11-12}}</ref>。

2019年9月，西澳大利亚州原住民女子受暴力殴打后向警方求助，但随后就因欠缴罚款被投入监狱。奎格利事后表示会在“数周内”递交修正法案。<ref>{{cite web | last = Hirini | first = Rangi | date = 2019-09-24 | url = https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/nitv-news/article/2019/09/24/aboriginal-unpaid-fines-western-australia | title = Aboriginal robbery victim jailed for unpaid fines after seeking police help | work = Special Broadcasting Service | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201030052415/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/nitv-news/article/2019/09/24/aboriginal-unpaid-fines-western-australia | archive-date = 2020-10-30 | dead-url = no}}</ref>法案在同月提出<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/sep/25/wa-repeals-laws-on-jailing-for-unpaid-fines | title = Western Australia repeals laws on jailing for unpaid fines | last = Wahlquist | first = Calla | date = 2019-09-24 | newspaper = Guardian Australia | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200628001232/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/sep/25/wa-repeals-laws-on-jailing-for-unpaid-fines | archive-date = 2020-06-28 | dead-url = no}}</ref>，2020年6月19日[[御准|御准]]。次日，该州所有欠缴罚款人员的逮捕令撤销，不允许再发出同类逮捕令<ref>{{cite web | title = Fines, Penalties and Infringement Notices Enforcement Amendment Bill 2019 | archive-date = 2020-06-17 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.parliament.wa.gov.au/parliament/bills.nsf/BillProgressPopup?openForm&ParentUNID=3DEEE1518D8036C54825848100052ECE | website = Parliament of Western Australia | access-date = 2021-02-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200617150344/https://www.parliament.wa.gov.au/parliament/bills.nsf/BillProgressPopup?openForm&ParentUNID=3DEEE1518D8036C54825848100052ECE}}</ref>。

